#Functions

#Shuffles array elements in a random order i.e. [1,2,3] -> [2,1,3]
def shuffle(array):
    return sorted(array, key=lambda k: random.random())


# Normal Curve
def N(x,mu,stdev):
    constant = 1/(stdev*np.sqrt(2*np.pi))
    arg1 = -(x - mu)**2
    arg2 = 2*stdev**2
    return constant * np.exp(arg1/arg2)


# Initializing step

#(Initializing mu_hat)

def init_mu_hat(X,K):
    shuffle_X = shuffle(X)
    mu_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        mu_hat.append(shuffle_X[i])
    return mu_hat


#(Initializing var_hat)

def init_var_hat(X,K):
    var = np.var(X)
    var_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        var_hat.append(var)
    return var_hat

#(Initalizing phi_hat)

def init_phi_hat(X,K):
    phi_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        phi_hat.append(1/K)
    return phi_hat

mu_hat = init_mu_hat(X,K)
var_hat = init_var_hat(X,K)
phi_hat = init_phi_hat(X,K)


# E-step

def gamma(i,k):
    num = (phi_hat[k])*N(X[i], mu_hat[k], np.sqrt(var_hat[k]))
    array = []
    for j in range(K):
        array.append(phi_hat[j]*N(X[i],mu_hat[j], np.sqrt(var_hat[j])))
    den = sum(array)
    return num/den

def make_matrix(K):
    gamma_matrix = np.zeros([K, len(X)-1])
    for i in range(K):
        for j in range(len(X)-1):
            gamma_matrix[i,j] = gamma(j,i)
    return np.transpose(gamma_matrix)

# M-step

def phi_func(k):
    N = len(X)
    array = []
    for i in range(N-1):
        array.append(gamma_matrix[i,k])
    return (1/N)*sum(array)

#gives a new phi_hat vector
def new_phi(K):
    phi_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        phi_hat.append(phi_func(i))
    return phi_hat

def mu_func(k):
    N = len(X)
    array1 = []
    array2 = []
    for i in range(N-1):
        array1.append(X[i] * gamma_matrix[i,k])
        array2.append(gamma_matrix[i,k])
    return sum(array1)/sum(array2)

#gives a new mu_hat vector
def new_mu(K):
    mu_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        mu_hat.append(mu_func(i))
    return mu_hat


def var_func(k):
    N = len(X)
    def num(i,k):
        return (gamma_matrix[i,k])*((X[i] - mu_func(k))**2)
    array1 = []
    array2 = []
    for i in range(N-1):
        array1.append(num(i,k))
        array2.append(gamma_matrix[i,k])
    return sum(array1)/sum(array2)

#gives a new var_hat vector
def new_var(K):
    var_hat = []
    for i in range(K):
        var_hat.append(var_func(i))
    return var_hat

start = datetime.datetime.now()

phi_array = [phi_hat]
mu_array = [mu_hat]
var_array = [var_hat]


# This FOR loop is the EM algorithm part of the Gaussian Mixture model
for i in range(it):
    # E-step
    gamma_matrix = make_matrix(K)
    
    # M-step
    phi_hat = new_phi(K)
    mu_hat = new_mu(K)
    var_hat = new_var(K)

    #Keeping a record of iterations
    phi_array.append(phi_hat)
    mu_array.append(mu_hat)
    var_array.append(var_hat)


print('phi_hat = ', phi_hat)
print('mu_hat = ', mu_hat)
print('var_hat = ', var_hat)
print('stdev_hat = ', np.sqrt(var_hat))

finish = datetime.datetime.now()
print(' ')
print('It took (time = ',finish-start, ') to compute GMM')

#Animating the EM Algorithm

fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.axes(xlim=(-10, 20), ylim=(0, 20))

line1, = ax.plot([], [], lw=2)
line2, = ax.plot([], [], lw=2)
line3, = ax.plot([], [], lw=2)
line4, = ax.plot([], [], lw=2)

%matplotlib inline

def init():
    line1.set_data([], [])
    line2.set_data([], [])
    line3.set_data([], [])
    line4.set_data([], [])
    return (line1,line2,line3,line4)

def animate(i):
    x = np.linspace(-10, 20, 1000)
    y1 = (n*(phi_array[i])[0])*N(x, (mu_array[i])[0] ,np.sqrt( (var_array[i])[0] ))
    y2 = (n*(phi_array[i])[1])*N(x, (mu_array[i])[1] ,np.sqrt( (var_array[i])[1] ))
    y3 = (n*(phi_array[i])[2])*N(x, (mu_array[i])[2] ,np.sqrt( (var_array[i])[2] ))
    y4 = y1 + y2 + y3
    line1.set_data(x, y1)
    line2.set_data(x, y2)
    line3.set_data(x, y3)
    line4.set_data(x, y4)
    return (line1, line2, line3,line4)

anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init,
                               frames=60, interval=100, 
                               blit=True)
HTML(anim.to_jshtml())
